<DOC><DOCNO> AP880714-0050 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-14-88 0533EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r p PM-PoliticalQuotes     07-14 0167</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Political Quotes,150</SECOND><HEAD>Quotes From the Campaign Trail</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Here are some comments from the presidentialcampaign trail:</TEXT><TEXT>      MICHAEL DUKAKIS, on Jesse Jackson: ``We want him to play animportant role in the campaign. We want his support. We hope andexpect he will be very much involved with us in the campaign andafterwards.''      JESSE JACKSON, hinting at a possible floor fight over the vicepresidential nomination at the Democratic National Convention:``I'm not suggesting that I will compete for a place on the ticketbut the floor is wide open on Thursday night when therecommendation is made.''      SEN. LLOYD BENTSEN, on how he would serve as vice president toDukakis: ``As vice president of the United States, I would give himthe very best counsel I could when I agreed or disagreed on theissues. But there's only one president of the United States andhe's the man that bears the ultimate responsibility and pays theultimate price.''</TEXT></DOC>